6 bao buns
300 g Beef Rump
1 packet Mayonnaise
1 Cucumber
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 Spring Onion
2 packet Potato
1 packet Sichuan Garlic Paste
1 Radish
1 drizzle olive oil
¼ cup water
1 drizzle vinegar (white wine or red wine)

• See 'Top Steak Tips!' (below).
• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until just tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, slice cucumber into sticks.
• Thinly slice radish and spring onion.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook spring onion until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a small bowl. Set aside.
• Season beefrump with salt and pepper.

• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef for 4-5 minutes each side for medium-rare, or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate to rest.
• Remove pan from heat, add Sichuan garlic paste and the water, then stir to combine.
• Once the beef has finished resting, thinly slice beef, then return to the pan. Toss to coat.

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, radish, cucumber and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• When the fries are done, add spring onion oil to the tray and toss to coat.

• Place bao buns on a microwave-safe plate and cover with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave on high for 1 minute. Set aside to rest, 1 minute.

• Gently halve bao buns and spread with mayonnaise.
• Fill with Sichuan garlic beef and cucumber and radish salad. Spoon over any remaining sauce.
• Serve with spring onion fries and remaining salad. Enjoy!